defaultRheumatology is a multidisciplinary branch of medicine that deals with the investigation, diagnosis and management of patients with rheumatic diseases and other musculoskeletal conditions.default This incorporates over 200 disorders affecting joints, muscles and soft tissues, including autoimmune disorders and spinal pain. A significant number of rheumatic conditions also affect other organ systems
