defaultNAO report in 2009 
defaultfound that this happens with only 10% of patients
default.
default This is in part due to delays in being seen by a rheumatologist and partly due to local differences in the access level to key drugs.
default The average delay in the UK in GP surgeries is around nine months, by which time joint damage in aggressive disease has already occurred.
